[bold][italic][double-underline]Field Manual 42-B: Interdimensional Incident Response[/underline][/italic][/intensity]

[bold][underline]Preamble[/underline][/intensity]

This manual describes standard operating procedure for[bold] Class-III multiverse
[bold]incursions[/intensity], as adopted by the[italic] Intergalactic Committee on Narrative Integrity[/italic]
(ICNI). All personnel are required to read it twice, sign the waiver, and
memorize Section 4 before their next shift.

[dim][italic][dim]│ [/intensity][dim][italic]"The universe is not only stranger than we imagine, it is stranger than we can
[dim]│ [/intensity][dim][italic][dim][italic]be reimbursed for."
[dim]│ [/intensity][dim][italic]
[dim]│ [/intensity][dim][italic]— Admiral Ackbar, 2387 budget hearing
[dim]│ [/intensity][dim][italic]
[dim][italic][dim]│ │ [/intensity][dim][italic][dim][italic]Accounting note: next time, please file form[italic][bold] W-42B[/intensity][dim][/italic][italic] in triplicate.
[/italic][italic][/intensity][dim][/italic][/intensity]
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

[bold][underline]Section 1 — Crossover Classification[/underline][/intensity]

The following incursion types have been observed in the last[strike] fiscal quarter[/strike]
epoch:

┌───────┬──────────────────────────────────────┬──────────────┐
│ [bold]Class[/intensity] │ [bold]              Example               [/intensity] │ [bold]Threat Level[/intensity] │
├───────┼──────────────────────────────────────┼──────────────┤
│ Alpha │ Gandalf at Comic-Con                 │ Low          │
├───────┼──────────────────────────────────────┼──────────────┤
│ Beta  │ Spock attending a quidditch match    │ Medium       │
├───────┼──────────────────────────────────────┼──────────────┤
│ Gamma │ A TARDIS inside a Death Star reactor │ CRITICAL     │
└───────┴──────────────────────────────────────┴──────────────┘

See [underline]the full classification taxonomy[/underline][dim] (https://example.invalid/icni/taxonomy)[/intensity] for
additional detail, or browse the quick reference at [underline]
[underline]https://example.invalid/icni/quick-ref[/underline][dim] (https://example.invalid/icni/quick-ref)[/intensity].

[bold][underline]Section 2 — Initial Response[/underline][/intensity]

Upon detecting an incursion, operatives should:

1. Confirm the breach using the[code] multiverse-scan --now[/color] command.
2. Assess threat level per Section 1.
3. Notify your local liaison.[bold] Do not[/intensity] attempt to resolve Alpha-class
   incursions personally — they typically resolve themselves once coffee is
   offered.
4. File an incident report, even if the incident was "just a cat".

[bold]Example Scan Output[/intensity]

[code]  $ multiverse-scan --now
  [ok] scanning timelines 1..2^64
  [warn] anomaly at (42, 7, 1977)
  [critical] The One Ring detected inside a replicator unit
[/color]
If the output looks garbled, try the unflagged variant:

[code]  multiverse-scan
[/color]
[bold][underline]Section 3 — Field Kit[/underline][/intensity]

Operatives carry the following items at all times:

• A[italic] sonic screwdriver[/italic] (standard issue)
• One (1)[code] phaser[/color], set to stun
• A small notebook labelled[bold] Don't Panic[/intensity]
• Emergency rations, consisting of:
  • Lembas bread
  • Replicator chits
  • A single chocolate frog, for morale

    Morale is critical on extended assignments. Personnel who neglect their
    chocolate frog ration have been observed to sulk, at which point rescue
    teams report a measurable drop in[italic] snark throughput[/italic].

[bold]Escalation Chain[/intensity]

Incidents escalate in the following order:

1. Field operative
2. Shift supervisor
3. Regional coordinator
  1. First deputy
  2. Second deputy (Tuesdays only)
4. ICNI council

[image: Official ICNI seal][dim] (https://example.invalid/icni/seal.png)[/intensity]

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

[bold][underline]Appendix A — Poetry Corner[/underline][/intensity]

By long-standing tradition, every manual concludes with a verse. The following
was composed by R2-D2 during his tenure as guest editor:

Beep boop beep, the stars align,
The Force and phasers intertwine,
One does not simply walk to warp,
So set your course, and mind the sharp.

[italic]End of document.[/italic]
